What you need to know:

The 1-2 victory for the Japanese manufacturer now headed by former WRC driver Finn Jari-Matti Latvala as team principal, who took over from Tommi Makinen, a two-time Safari champion last year, promises a highly competitive season for main challengers Hyundai and Ford who got  mixed results in Monte Carlo.  Belgian Thierry Neuville gave Hyundai a podium finish to split a possible 1-2-3 for Toyota after Finn Kalle Rovanperä’ suffered a puncture in his Toyota Yaris on the final day  in an impressive drive with a new compatriot co-driver, Martijn Waydaeghe following the unavailability of his regular partner countryman Nicholas Gilsoul.